-- SMBC to buy Citi Japan retail business in October - sources
-- By Taro Fuse
-- Wed Dec 24, 2014 12:31AM EST
-- None



TOKYO, Dec 24 (Reuters) - Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp (SMBC) will buy Citigroup Inc's <C.N> Japanese retail banking operations in October for about 40 billion yen ($332 million), people with knowledge of the matter said on Wednesday.

The Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group Inc <8316.T> unit will announce the long-awaited sale on Thursday, the sources said.